The paper deals with the problem of visual forensics and model attribution in the context of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and their ability to generate photorealistic images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques to learn GAN fingerprints and classify images as real or GAN-generated, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also presents experiments to show the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which involves training and fine-tuning machine learning models, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GANs to generate images, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of adversarial image perturbations, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
